# asr_finetuning/ — fine-tuned Whisper (the graded ML contribution)

Fine-tunes `openai/whisper-small` for Darija/Arabic STT (HF `Seq2SeqTrainer`).
Design: `docs/tdd/TDD-01-ASR-Whisper.md`; usage: `asr_finetuning/README.md`;
results: `docs/RESULTS_TDD-01.md`. Trained model: `Amassu/whisper-small-darija`
(WER 108→28.8%, CER 64→9.6% vs base on DODa).

## How to run
Run **from `asr_finetuning/`** (modules use the `src.` package prefix). Training
needs a GPU (Colab/Kaggle) — not runnable on a CPU-only box.

```bash
cd asr_finetuning
pip install -r requirements.txt
huggingface-cli login                 # gated datasets (DODa, Common Voice)
bash scripts/smoke_test.sh            # end-to-end sanity run
python -m src.train --config config/doda_darija.yaml          # Darija fine-tune
python -m src.evaluate_model --config config/doda_darija.yaml --model.name <ckpt_or_hub_id>
```

- **Dotted CLI overrides:** any config field, e.g.
  `--training.max_steps 5000 --dataset.config ar --model.name openai/whisper-medium`
  (handled by `src/config.py`).
- **Eval = the graded metric:** always report **WER/CER of fine-tuned vs. base**
  on the **same** split (apples-to-apples). Never fabricate numbers — if a run
  fails, report the real error.
- Modules: `config.py` (loader) · `data.py` (load/preprocess + collator) ·
  `metrics.py` (WER/CER) · `train.py` · `evaluate_model.py` ·
  `transcribe.py` (`WhisperTranscriber`, the serving interface the backend calls).
- No test framework; `scripts/smoke_test.sh` is the de-facto check.
